TOM BYRUM: Cooler day, and there was a little more wind when we started out of a different direction.  No. 1 was a little left-to-right and hurting and 2 was straight in.
It played kind of tough starting out I thought.  But you know, then we kind of got into it.  It was set up a little bit harder I thought, too.  The pin placements were a little bit more closer to the edges and things like that.  But still, good score if you're hitting good shots.  I just didn't quite have the same shot-making today as I did yesterday.
